<HEADLINE>
HSUEHSHAN TUNNEL TO BE CLOSED FOR DISASTER CONTROL DRILLS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  April 17 (CNA) 04/17/07  20:05:14 (By Elizabeth Hsu)
</P>
<P>
The Hsuehshan Tunnel on the Peiyi Freeway will be closed for a
four-hour period April 23 and another four-hour period April 25
for seasonal drills focusing on disaster prevention and control
in the longest tunnel in Asia, officials of the Taiwan Area
National Expressway Bureau announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The provisional closure, to take place 9 p.m. to 1 a.m. April 23
and 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. April 25, will affect the freeway between
Pinglin in Taipei County and Toucheng in Yilan County in
northeastern Taiwan, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
The bureau suggested that drivers planning to travel to Yilan
from Taipei at that time to leave the freeway at the Shiting
interchange and take highway 106 to Pinglin before taking
provincial highway 9 to Yilan.
</P>
<P>
Drivers from Yilan to Taipei can leave the freeway at the
Toucheng interchange and take provincial highway 9 to Pinglin
before taking the 106 to Shiting, where they can get back on the
freeway.
</P>
<P>
The 12.9 km Hsuehshan Tunnel was opened to traffic in June 2006
after 15 years of construction.
</P>
